From 934565b7817b85a341b88d23df7c90a28c62dd0a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 23:20:09 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] invoker: skip the sailjaild D-Bus query when sailjail is not
 installed

Every launch performs a synchronous D-Bus round-trip (bus connect +
method call + ServiceUnknown error reply) to org.sailfishos.sailjaild1
on systems that do not ship the sandboxing daemon. Sandbox enforcement
prepends /usr/bin/sailjail to the command anyway, so when that binary
does not exist the query can never lead anywhere: gate it on
access(SAILJAIL_PATH, X_OK) and drop the dead bus traffic from the
launch critical path.

Upstream-Status: Pending
---
 src/invoker/invoker.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/invoker/invoker.c b/src/invoker/invoker.c
index 2bc1143..9642a7d 100644
--- a/src/invoker/invoker.c
+++ b/src/invoker/invoker.c
@@ -1136,6 +1136,13 @@ int main(int argc, char *argv[])
         free(path);
     }
 
+    // Sandboxing needs the sailjail binary (it gets prepended to the
+    // command below). On systems that do not ship it, skip the sailjaild
+    // D-Bus query: it is a synchronous bus round-trip (connect + method
+    // call + error reply) on the critical path of every single launch.
+    if (args.sandboxing_id && access(SAILJAIL_PATH, X_OK) == -1)
+        args.sandboxing_id = NULL;
+
     // Application specific boosters are running in sandbox and can
     // thus launch only sandboxed processes, otherwise
     // If arguments don't define sailjail and sailjaild says the app must be sandboxed,
-- 
